Now, we can compute the current share price using the equation in step . 

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Current Share Price} 
 &=\dfrac{\text{DP}}{\text{(1 + r)}} + \dfrac{\text{LDP}}{\text{$(1 + r)^2$}} \\[10pt]
 &=\dfrac{\text{\$ 3.15}}{\text{(1 + 0.15)}} + \dfrac{\text{\$ 57}}{\text{$(1 + 0.15)^2$}} \\[10pt]
 &=\dfrac{\text{\$ 3.15}}{\text{(1.15)}} + \dfrac{\text{\$ 57}}{\text{$(1.15)^2$}} \\[10pt]
 &=\text{\$ 2.74} + \text{\$ 43.10}\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\textbf{\$ 45.84}}
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen, the current share price of the company is **$ 45.84**.
